This paper discusses the effectiveness of censorship in the context of the Internet and social media, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CR) and social media (cs.SI). The paper also uses data analysis to support its claims, which could fall under the categories of computational finance (cs.PF) and statistical analysis (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses legal measures to counteract censorship, which could fall under the category of cyber law (cs.CY).
